lines.text: Attachment A
QUESTIONS & ANSWERS
Question:
I noticed on the RBI Wood Fixtures reference sheet (black tab) that bases are not included with Standard RBI
Fixtures. Is this true
Answer:
No. Bases are included with all Standard RBI Fixtures (this was a misprint in the brochure). However, bases
should be ordered separately for Backbar RBI Fixtures.
Question:
What should I order if I want to remove 1 springload shelf on a 2' PM fixture and replace it with an illuminated
sign? There is a PM springload shelf above our space.
Answer:
You would order 1 of item #590795 (2' Small POS Box), 1 of item #592565 (2' POS Box/Retrofit Module S/L
Shelf), 1 of item #590522 (2' Standard/Small Light Kit) and 1 of item #595601 (6' RBI Extension Cord). The
transparency must be ordered separately
Question:
Answer:
Why did we stop packing transparencyes in the light kit?
The cost of each transparency has increased since the quality has been improved and in some kits there would
be as many as 9 transparencyes of which only one would be needed.
Question:
Will all RJR Retrofit Modules fit into RJR Wood Merchandisers?
Answer:
They will fit into all RJR Wood Fixtures except for one 3' fixture produced several years ago. The outside width
of the wood fixture that will accept the module is 36 '/16". If the fixture is not this measurement a new wood
fixture should be ordered. There is also a star decal located on the top left inside corner of the pack panel.
Question:
What should I do if I have a question about what will fit into a fixture?
Answer:
Each ROU and/or region has a person that was trained and can answer any questions that may arise.
Question:
The POS box will not fit flush to the bottom of the 2' PM springload shelf above it and the space is figured as RJR
space
Answer:
Remove the PM shelf directly above the POS Box and install item #592565 (2' POS Box/Retrofit Module Spring
load Shelf) onto the top of the POS box. Place the PM springload cartridges from the shelf you removed in the
new shelf and secure the carthages
Question:
How can I get the counting springload cartridges for other fixtures I have in my assignment?
Answer:
The counting springload cartridge will be available for ordering after sufficient inventories are reached. The first
priority will be to provide these cartridges to the RBI Fixtures and retrofit modules
Question:
Are the RBI Retrofit Components allocated?
Answer:
All items to support the RBI Program are not allocated. However, each region will have a roll out program that will
prioritize what calls should be worked first.
Question:
On all sets that were ordered with wire components, will the RBI items have to be ordered separately?
Answer:
No, if the fixtures were ordered as complete wire fixtures there will be one AOS number you will be able to order
that will include all the component parts that are necessary to change over to the RBI look.
Question:
Does the PM fixture require a different size POS card or transparency than the RJR fixture?
Answer:
No, using the clear POS cover as a template you can cut either side to fit.
Question:
Will the retrofit modules work on grid and slatwall?
Answer:
Yes, there will be a bracket available that works on both slatwall and Grid
Question:
Do I have to add the 1/4" for the interlocking channel for every module that I connect together vertically?
Answer:
No, you only add /4" for the bottom retrofit module.
Question:
Are POS cards packed with all Retrofit Modules, POS Boxes and Slimline Modules?
Answer:
Yes
Question:
Will the retrofit modules fit into wood fixtures that were shipped with 3P Wire Displays?
Answer:
No, these fixtures were produced 12" wider to accommodate the 3P Display. You should order a new fixture for
this account
Question:
I have an existing 2' Standard Profile RBI fixture and want to order lights. What should I order?
Answer:
You would order 3 each of item #593975 (2' Light Fixture Mounting Channel Kit), 1 of item #590501 (2' Enhanced
Light Kit), 2 each of item #590522 (2'Std/Small Light Kit) and 1 of item #595601 (6' RBI Extension cord).
Transparencyes must be ordered separately through the laptop under "Temporary Workplan POS".
Question:
Answer:
Will we have retrofit modules for B&W fixtures?
Yes, but due to the demand and quantity for modules to fit PM and RJRT fixtures, the B&W modules will be
handled on an "as needed" basis in the future. Details to be communicated later.
Source: https://www.industrydocuments.ucsf.edu/docs/hmjh0224
